taxonomicnotes: In Bishai and Khalil (1997), the taxonomic authority is "Geoffroy, 1827"
rationale: This species has a wide distribution, with no known major widespread threats. It is therefore listed as Least Concern. Regionally, it has been assessed as Vulnerable in northern Africa, Data Deficient in northeast Africa, and Least Concern in western Africa.
assessor: Azeroual, A., Entsua-Mensah, M., Getahun, A. & Lalèyè, P.
evaluator: Snoeks, J., Tweddle, D., Getahun, A., Lalèyè, P., Paugy, D., Zaiss, R., Fishar, M.R.A & Brooks, E.

taxonomicnotes: In Bishai and Khalil (1997), the taxonomic authority is "Cuvier & Valenciennes, 1840"
rationale: This species has a wide distribution, with no known major widespread threats. It is therefore listed as Least Concern. It has also been assessed regionally as Least Concern for central, east and west Africa. In northeast Africa it has been assessed as Data Deficient, and in north Africa it has been assessed as Vulnerable.
assessor: Azeroual, A., Entsua-Mensah, M., Getahun, A., Hanssens, M., Lalèyè, P. & Moelants, T.
evaluator: Snoeks, J., Tweddle, D., Getahun, A., Lalèyè, P., Paugy, D., Zaiss, R., Fishar, M.R.A & Brooks, E.
